r-deal-is-dead-3624589%5C%22%3EJoint%20Comprehensive%20Plan%20of%20Action%20(or%20the%20JCPOA)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20hailed%20as%20a%20victory%20of%20diplomacy%20over%20conflict%20to%20manage%20a%20delicate%20reality%20of%20the%20nuclearisation%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmiddle-east-remains-on-edge-as-israel-vows-response-to-iran-attack-5459127%5C%22%3Evolatile%20Middle%20East%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Idea%20Behind%20The%20Deal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%202015%20seems%20like%20a%20lifetime%20ago%2C%20and%20the%20future%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Firan-nuclear-talks-iran-nuclear-deal-iran-nuclear-talks-2015-success-is-never-guaranteed-us-missive-on-iran-nuclear-deal-talks-2802826%5C%22%3EJCPOA%20is%20bleak%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Under%20no%20means%20was%20the%20deal%20a%20perfect%20one.%20It%20was%20perhaps%20never%20meant%20to%20be%20perfect%20either.%20The%20idea%20behind%20the%20arrangement%20was%20to%20avoid%20conflict%20and%20find%20a%20political%20middle%20path%20to%20end%20not%20just%20a%20nuclear%20impasse%20but%20decades%20of%20isolation%20for%20Tehran.%20In%20exchange%20for%20checks%20and%20balances%20implemented%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fun-worried-israel-could-target-irans-nuclear-sites-urges-restraint-5451217%5C%22%3EInternational%20Atomic%20Energy%20Agency%20(IAEA)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Iran%20would%20benefit%20from%20the%20opening%20of%20its%20economy%20to%20global%20trade.%20However%2C%20everything%20changed%20in%202018%2C%20when%20newly%20empowered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftrump-announces-plan-to-pull-out-of-iran-nuclear-deal-despite-pleas-from-european-leaders-1849306%5C%22%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20long-standing%20critic%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20withdrew%20from%20it.%20Interestingly%2C%20access%20to%20nuclear%20technologies%20is%20not%20a%20new%20area%20of%20contestation%20for%20Iran.%20In%20fact%2C%20its%20first%20nuclear%20reactor%20to%20go%20critical%20in%201967%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20US%2C%20as%20part%20of%20its%20Atoms%20For%20Peace%20construct%20put%20forward%20by%20former%20US%20president%20Dwight%20D.%20Eisenhower%20in%201953.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20of%20Trump's%20erroneous%20and%20unilateral%20decision%20to%20withdraw%20was%20multi-layered.%20While%20it%20showcased%20partisan%20politics%20taking%20a%20stronger%20hold%20in%20Washington%2C%20it%20also%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20fundamentals%20and%20veracity%20of%20American%20security%20architecture%20for%20allies%20in%20Europe%20and%20Asia%20alike.%20But%20another%2C%20more%20serious%20outcome%2C%20which%20it%20may%20have%20pushed%2C%20was%20that%20the%20US%20exit%20also%20changed%20the%20landscape%20of%20Iranian%20domestic%20politics.%20During%20the%20negotiation%20period%2C%20the%20Iranian%20government%20was%20led%20by%20Hassan%20Rouhani%2C%20a%20moderate%2C%20and%20foreign%20minister%20Javad%20Zarif%2C%20who%2C%20educated%20across%20American%20institutions%2C%20had%20a%20level%20of%20outward-looking%20worldliness%20even%20as%20he%20was%20firmly%20rooted%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20Iran.%20The%20JCPOA%20exit%20amplified%20and%20emboldened%20the%20conservatives%20and%20a%20long-standing%20view%20that%20the%20US%20could%20never%20be%20trusted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Straitened%20Path%20Forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20way%2C%20Iran's%20all-powerful%20Ayatollah%20Khamenei%20had%20uncharacteristically%20let%20his%20guard%20down%20and%20allowed%20for%20talks%20with%20the%20US.%20Trump's%20decision%20set%20back%20moderate%20politics%20in%20Iran%20by%20decades.%20This%20was%20further%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20despite%20initially%20suggesting%20a%20return%20to%20renegotiation%20with%20Iran%2C%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20get%20the%20process%20moving%20due%20to%20a%20host%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20headwinds%20by%20the%20Democrats%20and%20lobbying%20by%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20diplomacy%20and%20realpolitik%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20Iran's%20nuclearisation%20threatens%20to%20become%20more%20critical%20and%20uncontainable%20than%20ever.%20While%20earlier%20Iran%20used%20its%20programme%20to%20both%20strengthen%20its%20strategic%20requirements%20and%20use%20it%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20leverage%20against%20the%20West%2C%20the%20confrontation%20with%20Israel%20last%20week%2C%20a%20West-aided%20air%20defence%20alliance%20surrounding%20Israel%2C%20with%20a%20probability%20of%20participation%20from%20certain%20Arab%20states%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20Israel%20is%20already%20widely%20viewed%20as%20the%20only%20(undeclared)%20nuclear%20power%20in%20the%20region%2C%20may%20make%20the%20nuclear%20deal%20a%20document%20of%20historic%20insignificance.%20And%20if%20so%2C%20the%20consequences%20could%20be%20dire%20in%20the%20long%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIran's%20Capabilities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%20is%20a%20nuclear%20threshold%20state.%20There%20are%20various%20parameters%20predicting%20how%20far%20it%20really%20is%20from%20building%20a%20nuclear%20warhead.%20Its%20nuclear%20facilities%2C%20such%20as%20Natanz%20and%20Fordow%2C%20the%20fulcrum%20of%20both%20its%20nuclear%20capacities%20and%20the%20international%20community's%20worries%2C%20are%20known%20to%20be%20producing%20enriched%20uranium%20almost%20nearing%20weapons-grade.%20The%20recent%20attacks%20by%20Iran%20against%20Israel%20using%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20and%20the%20use%20of%20similar%20missile%20equipment%20by%20Iranian-supported%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20Houthis%20-%20along%20with%20Tehran%20successfully%20launching%20satellites%20into%20low-Earth%20orbit%20using%20technologies%20like%20the%20ones%20used%20in%20its%20Inter-Continent%20Ballistic%20Missiles%20(ICBMs)%20-%20show%20consistency%20in%20capability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Iranian%20missile%20programme%20has%20grown%20since%20its%20inception%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20under%20the%20tutelage%20of%20Hassan%20Tehrani%20Moghaddam%2C%20a%20military%20officer%20with%20the%20powerful%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps'%20(IRGC)%20aerospace%20wing%2C%20who%20also%20reportedly%20sought%20expertise%20from%20North%20Korea%2C%20a%20country%20that%20conducted%20its%20first%20nuclear%20test%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERipple%20Effects%20In%20Middle%20East%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Iran%20may%20still%20be%20far%20away%20from%20conducting%20any%20nuclear%20tests%20-%20it%20might%20never%20even%20actually%20do%20so%20-%20it%20can%20still%20attain%20nuclear%20capability%20through%20the%20production%20of%20low-yield%20tactical%20nuclear%20weapons%20that%20are%20designed%20for%20use%20in%20conventional%20battlefields.%20If%20Iran%20does%20attain%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20and%20Israel%20consequently%20goes%20public%20with%20its%20own%2C%20then%20Saudi%20Arabia%20is%20most%20likely%20to%20follow%20suit.%20In%20an%20interview%20in%20September%202023%2C%20Saudi%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20hinted%20that%20if%20Iran%20goes%20nuclear%2C%20the%20Kingdom%20will%20%26quot%3Bhave%20to%20get%20one%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20Pakistan%20is%20the%20only%20Islamic%20nation%20with%20nuclear%20weapons%3B%20for%20long%2C%20it%20has%20been%20believed%20that%20if%20Saudi%20Arabia%20ever%20seeks%20nuclear%20weapons%20capabilities%2C%20it%20would%20get%20help%20from%20Islamabad.%20In%202013%2C%20a%20BBC%20report%20claimed%20that%20intelligence%20accessed%20by%20NATO%20officials%20highlighted%20nuclear%20weapons%20made%20for%20Saudi%20Arabia%20by%20Pakistan%20were%20%26quot%3Bsitting%20ready%20for%20delivery%26quot%3B.%20Despite%20the%20Pakistani%20establishment's%20denials%20over%20the%20years%2C%20it%20is%20still%20widely%20believed%20that%20the%20timeframe%20within%20which%20Saudi%20Arabia%20can%20attain%20nuclear%20weapons%20is%20very%20small%20due%20to%20its%20strategic%20partnership%20with%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIran%20Has%20'Options'%20Today%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20question%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20is%20both%20technological%20and%20political.%20In%20the%20former%20context%2C%20Iran%20still%20has%20a%20lot%20to%20achieve.%20While%20its%20success%20in%20asymmetric%20warfare%20and%20the%20development%20of%20ballistic%20missiles%20and%20drones%20is%20in%20the%20news%2C%20it%20must%20be%20remembered%20that%20very%20few%20of%20these%20military%20interventions%20are%20hi-tech.%20The%20drones%20used%20by%20Iran%2C%20which%20have%20also%20been%20supplied%20to%20Russia%20for%20use%20against%20Ukraine%2C%20are%20low-cost%20and%20effective%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20known%20to%20cause%20large-scale%20damage.%20The%20nuisance%20value%20here%20outdoes%20the%20tactical%20value.%20The%20missiles%2C%20too%2C%20are%20yet%20to%20prove%20their%20mettle%20in%20combat%2C%20with%20most%20of%20them%20being%20successfully%20taken%20down%20in%20the%20recent%20exchange%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20politically%2C%20Iran%20would%20be%20surer%20today%20about%20the%20near-absolute%20security%20a%20nuclear%20arsenal%20provides.%20North%20Korea%2C%20its%20initial%20collaborator%2C%20is%20perhaps%20a%20good%20example.%20The%20political%20direction%20Tehran%20will%20seek%20going%20forward%20will%20not%20be%20easy%2C%20as%20some%20predict.%20Iran%20would%20not%20want%20to%20be%20a%20hermit%20state%20and%20will%20find%20success%20in%20its%20economic%20and%20political%20outreach%20with%20the%20likes%20of%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20along%20with%20others%20in%20the%20Global%20South.%20Unlike%20previous%20decades%2C%20Tehran%20has%20options.%20But%20despite%20those%2C%20it%20would%20still%20seek%20a%20workable%20solution%20with%20the%20West%20at%20some%20point%20in%20the%20future%2C%20even%20if%20the%20chances%20for%20that%20are%20next%20to%20nil%20currently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUncertainty%20Reigns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20for%20Israel%2C%20nuclear%20power%20in%20the%20region%20is%20a%20big%20red%20line.%20Iran%20was%20of%20course%20not%20the%20only%20such%20example.%20Israel%20has%20conducted%20airstrikes%20to%20disable%20the%20nuclear%20programmes%20of%20both%20Iraq%20(1981)%20and%20Syria%20(2007)%20in%20the%20past.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20Israel%20has%20conducted%20several%20covert%20operations%20in%20Iran%20against%20its%20nuclear%20sites%2C%20scientists%2C%20and%20personnel%20to%20significantly%20set%20back%20the%20Iranian%20programme.%20A%20return%20of%20such%20actions%2C%20scaled%20up%20by%20many%20times%2C%20should%20be%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20conventional%20war%20remains%20a%20looming%20threat%2C%20external%20pressures%20on%20Israel%20may%20dissuade%20it%20from%20setting%20out%20on%20such%20a%20path.%20The%20issue%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%20remains%20unresolved%2C%20and%20at%20this%20moment%2C%20even%20if%20Iran%20does%20not%20scale%20up%2C%20it%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20scale%20down%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%5BKabir%20Taneja%20is%20a%20Fellow%20with%20the%20Strategic%20Studies%20Programme%20at%20the%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20'The%20ISIS%20Peril%3A%20The%20World's%20Most%20Feared%20Terror%20Group%20and%20its%20Shadow%20on%20South%20Asia'%20(Penguin%20Viking%2C%202019)%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713355020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Ftmbgd1bk_us-sanctions-on-iran_625x300_17_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Firan-israel-middle-east-becom