Singh%20had%20liberalised%20numerous%20laws%2C%20including%20the%20company%20law%20and%20the%20Trade%20Practices%20Act%20MRTP.%20However%2C%20he%20highlighted%20that%20subsequent%20governments%20over%20the%20following%20three%20decades%20did%20not%20see%20the%20need%20to%20amend%20the%20Industry%20(Development%20and%20Regulation)%20Act%2C%201951.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20response%20came%20after%20the%20bench%20criticised%20of%20the%20IDRA%2C%201951%2C%20describing%20it%20as%20archaic%20and%20indicative%20of%20the%20restrictive%20policies%20of%20the%20'licence%20raj'%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Mehta%20emphasised%20that%20despite%20the%20winds%20of%20change%20brought%20by%20economic%20reforms%2C%20the%20IDRA%20remained%20untouched%2C%20allowing%20the%20Centre%20to%20maintain%20significant%20control%20over%20various%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201991%2C%20faced%20with%20a%20foreign%20reserves%20crisis%2C%20the%20Narasimha%20Rao-led%20government%20introduced%20three%20transformative%20economic%20reforms%3A%20globalisation%2C%20liberalisation%2C%20and%20privatisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Mehta%20also%20clarified%20that%20the%20Centre's%20withdrawal%20from%20controlling%20industries%20did%20not%20indicate%20a%20lack%20of%20regulatory%20authority.%20He%20stressed%20that%20the%20Centre%20retained%20the%20power%20to%20regulate%20industries%20in%20the%20national%20interest%2C%20particularly%20during%20emergencies%20like%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%20Mr%20Mehta%20elaborated%20that%20had%20the%20Union%20government%20not%20had%20the%20authority%20to%20regulate%20industrial%20alcohol%2C%20especially%20for%20producing%20hand%20sanitizers%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20robust%20response%20to%20the%20crisis%20would%20have%20been%20compromised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713353100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fqrs9cq9_manmohan-singh_625x300_17_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fw